					<description><![CDATA[Outstanding. I&#039;m in the middle of writing an article on budgeting your energy that fits in well with this.

My wife and I are very different. She&#039;s an introvert and home-maker (she&#039;s makes the heck out of our home) and I&#039;m a weird mixed extrovert who likes to make up for the energy I spend with small groups of people by being alone or working.

We both handle our refills very differently, and we&#039;ve realized that we have to be more serious about the care with which we follow a budget for our energy so we can be the most loving and effective people to each other and our children. We would wing it for years, but we&#039;d experience this cumalative stress shutdown and find ourselves reeling from the experience for weeks.

It&#039;s hard to admit that we&#039;re limited people, but obviously we are. I&#039;m hoping that as I mature into my late thirties this will begin to stick even more.

Great articles and reminders on these issues. I&#039;m really thankful for them.

Happy Thanksgiving!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Outstanding. I&#8217;m in the middle of writing an article on budgeting your energy that fits in well with this.</p>
<p>My wife and I are very different. She&#8217;s an introvert and home-maker (she&#8217;s makes the heck out of our home) and I&#8217;m a weird mixed extrovert who likes to make up for the energy I spend with small groups of people by being alone or working.</p>
<p>We both handle our refills very differently, and we&#8217;ve realized that we have to be more serious about the care with which we follow a budget for our energy so we can be the most loving and effective people to each other and our children. We would wing it for years, but we&#8217;d experience this cumalative stress shutdown and find ourselves reeling from the experience for weeks.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s hard to admit that we&#8217;re limited people, but obviously we are. I&#8217;m hoping that as I mature into my late thirties this will begin to stick even more.</p>
<p>Great articles and reminders on these issues. I&#8217;m really thankful for them.</p>
<p>Happy Thanksgiving!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
