					<description><![CDATA[Anytime I hear someone speak in terms of buckets... I&#039;m reminded of a book we read to our kids, &quot;How Full is Your Bucket?&quot; by Tom Rath and Mary Rechmeyer (2009).  It&#039;s a very short but insightful read.  The story focuses on how our actions and interactions - both positive and negative have an impact on the contents of our buckets...  a great reminder to us as parents and our kids to reflect on whether we&#039;re adding or taking away from each other.  Runs parallel with your concept of cumulative stress...  check it out!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Anytime I hear someone speak in terms of buckets&#8230; I&#8217;m reminded of a book we read to our kids, &#8220;How Full is Your Bucket?&#8221; by Tom Rath and Mary Rechmeyer (2009).  It&#8217;s a very short but insightful read.  The story focuses on how our actions and interactions &#8211; both positive and negative have an impact on the contents of our buckets&#8230;  a great reminder to us as parents and our kids to reflect on whether we&#8217;re adding or taking away from each other.  Runs parallel with your concept of cumulative stress&#8230;  check it out!</p>
