					<description><![CDATA[The bucket stays fuller longer when it is properly balanced. The last five years of my life have been out of whack -- increasing debt, unstable income, 18-hour workdays, demanding employers -- and I have often ignored my health and happiness just to keep hearth and home together. I thought once things got better (as they have) I&#039;d immediately feel better, but that ain&#039;t so, and now I realize why. I need to make a concentrated effort to refill my bucket (and hope it has not got a hole in it!). Thanks Mr. Clear, for the clarity.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The bucket stays fuller longer when it is properly balanced. The last five years of my life have been out of whack &#8212; increasing debt, unstable income, 18-hour workdays, demanding employers &#8212; and I have often ignored my health and happiness just to keep hearth and home together. I thought once things got better (as they have) I&#8217;d immediately feel better, but that ain&#8217;t so, and now I realize why. I need to make a concentrated effort to refill my bucket (and hope it has not got a hole in it!). Thanks Mr. Clear, for the clarity.</p>
